description: Inflation is the rise in prices over time. The rate of inflation is how quickly prices have gone up. We know what the rate of inflation is because each month the prices of around 700 goods and services are checked by the Office for National Statistics. Find out more about the economy at www.bankofengland.co.uk/explainers
